    "created_at": "2024-05-24T15:05:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-05-24T15:05:10Z",
    "body": "You'd have to ask one of the people more intimately familiar with the project to be certain, but to the best of my knowledge starship takes a fundamentally different approach here. Tide seems to be a constantly monitoring the working directory, and updating as soon as possible. Starship, on the other hand, pulls the info when a command is issued and builds the modules in the prompt based on that",
