    "created_at": "2025-05-12T15:38:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-12T15:50:26Z",
    "body": "Had this issue a big part of 2024. Finally decided to look into it after confirming it wasn't the Mac or OMZ, and letting time pass in case of it being a bug.\n\n## Issue\nUndefined `$STARSHIP_CONFIG`.\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Starship installed via Homebrew\n> Using default Starship config path `~/.config/starship.toml`\n\n## Confirmed Fix\nImmediately the issue went away. New terminals load fast again and no timeout warning thrown.\n\nExplicitly defined env variable in `.zshrc` before loading Starship: `STARSHIP_CONFIG=${HOME}/.config/starship.toml`\n\n```\nSTARSHIP_CONFIG=${HOME}/.config/starship.toml\neval \"$(starship init zsh)\"\n```\n\nAdditionally setting `command_timeout = 1000` definitely made a difference when loading `.zshrc`. Not sure why that's taking that long, but betting on sourcing some additional resources there.\n\n> macOS 14.7.5\n> zsh 5.9\n> starship 1.23.0",
    "author_association": "NONE",
